    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-02-11T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-02-11T18:00:00-05:00" n="531"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d531">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">819.51A/–: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Panama</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Price</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-02-11T18:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 11, 1921—6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>8. Mr. John S. Hord, former Collector Internal Revenue in the Philippine Islands
                    and past President of the Bank of the Philippine Islands, is recommended by
                    Department to succeed Mr. Ruan as Fiscal Agent. Please inform President Porras
                    that Mr. Hord has <pb facs="0700" n="604" xml:id="pg_604"/> been selected from
                    among a number of suitable persons as being the best qualified. He speaks
                    Spanish well and is highly recommended by Doctor Rowe.<note n="4"
                        xml:id="d531fn4">Leo S. Rowe, Director General, Pan American Union.</note>
                    Mr. Hord is willing to go to Panama under the same conditions as Mr. Ruan but
                    desires to return to the United States for one month in May to settle personal
                    matters.</p>
                <p>Please cable early reply as Mr. Hord desires to be informed at an early date of
                    the President’s decision in view of other arrangements which he has pending.
                    Cable also date of Ruan’s sailing and port of landing in the United States.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Colby</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
